      "term": "calorists",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "A person who studied or advocated the caloric theory of heat (an old scientific view that heat is a fluid-like substance called caloric).",
          "examples": [
            "Calorists in the 18th century debated whether heat consisted of caloric."
